2016-06-30	Bogdan Drozdowski <bogdandr@op.pl>

	* JYMAG version 1.5:
	  This is mostly a bugfix and maintenenace release. Updated unit tests
	  (Mockito-1.10.x now required). Improvements to the build system.
	  Fixes to capabilities' scan and port scan. Other minor improvements.
	  Documentation updated.
	* test/SerialPortStub.java: Improved functionality of the stub -
	  should now return the saved data.
	* test/DataTransporterTest.java: Using Mockito to instantiate the
	  required classes, enabled some basic unit tests for transmission
	  classes.
	* TransferUtils.java (sendFileAsCommands): added null check for "f"
	* TransferUtils.java (isAllowedType): simplified the method
	* TransferUtils.java, Utils.java: added missing "NOI18N"s
	* Makefile: added new Timestamping Authority URLs (commented-out).
	  Removing generated files in the "setup" directory during
	  "make clean". Making the "dist-bin" and "installer" targets depend
	  on unit tests' results. Not signing an already-signed installer.
	  Non-phony targets depend on the Makefile. Touching the JAR file
	  after build (ant doesn't do this automatically). Digitally signing
	  the PDF manuals. Deleting the temporary distribution directories
	  in case they exist before the distribution is built. Touching the
	  exclusion file before each TAR packaging. Deleting some of the old
	  target distribution files before copying new ones.
	* Utils.java: using unmodifiable maps for the file type maps.
	* Utils.java, TransferUtils.java, MainWindow.java: using Maps
	  instead of Hashtables.
	* DataTransporter.java (open), PhoneAlarm.java (PhoneAlarm, setTime,
	  setDays): throwing IllegalArgumentExceptions instead of
	  NullPointerExceptions.
	* Utils.java (convertCalendarMonthToReal, convertRealMonthToCalendar):
	  new methods for converting Calendar month values to real month
	  numbers and vice-versa.
	* PhoneAlarm.java (PhoneAlarm, parseReponse): using
	  Utils.convertRealMonthToCalendar()
	* PhoneAlarm.java (getDateString): using convertCalendarMonthToReal()
	* PhoneAlarm.java (PhoneAlarm, setDays, parseReponse): using
	  Integer.valueOf().
	* PhoneAlarm.java: added new methods for converting String and integer
	  arrays to sets of Integers and using these methods in parsers.
	* Utils.java (isAllowableSpeed, isAllowableDataBits): simplified code
	* CommandLineParser.java (parse): fixed exception messages, updated
	  web addresses of the program.
	* TransferUtils.java (scanPorts): call "afterPort" only once, in the
	  "finally" block. Fixed closing the port on error so that there are
	  no lock files and subsequent errors.
	* MainWindow.java (MainWindow), JYMAGTransferHandler (importData,
	  importSingleFile): don't use the extended "for" loop syntax.
	* DataTransporter.java (getCapabilities): add checking for String
	  index bounds, in case no answer is received.
	* ConfigFile.java (write): use a BufferedWriter to handle newlines.
	* MainWindow.java (scanButtonActionPerformed): moved the constant
	  Runnable to a class field.
	* TransferParameters.java: a new class for serial port parameters,
	  to be passed to TransferUtils.
	* test: temporarily removed the test for the TransferUtils class
	  (was never used anyway, will be rebuilt in the future).
	* manual: updated the tabs' and windows' screenshots
	* README, manual/*/readme.html: added default values of command-line
	  options, where applicable.
	* CommandLineParser.java: fixed indentation of the help message
	* JYMAGTransferHandler.java (importData): returning "true" (import
	  succeeded) also for Linux-flavoured drag&drops.
	* TransferUtils.java (performOperation): improved checking if the work
	  is done, because the UI could hang

2014-08-15	Bogdan Drozdowski <bogdandr@op.pl>

	* JYMAG version 1.4:
	  Code cleanup. Minor fixes and optimizations to the application.
	  Better error reporting. Major improvements to the build system.
	* Makefile: fixed the dependencies of the Windows(tm) installer and
	  the JAR file, fixed generating the EXE files (more automatic and
	  system-independent now), added links to external software. Added
	  signing the JAR file and the installer. Fixed dependencies of the
	  jymag-en.exe file. Common file and directory names now in variables.
	* DataTransporter.java: changed the constant fields with the headers
	  to static fields.
	* TransferUtils.java (sendFileAsCommands): catching Exceptions in
	  Thread.sleep.
	* *.java: added curly braces in conditionals.
	* PhoneAlarm.java (parseReponse): optimization: evaluating the
	  matcher groups just once.
	* COPYING, manual: added the MIT license for the EXE programs that
	  start JYMAG (jymag*.exe).
	* Utils.EscKeyListener (keyTyped): calling the window listeners
	  manually before calling dispose on the frame. This way, the
	  listeners are certainly called and pressing the Esc key now deletes
	  the log file when it's empty (that's the way it should be).
	* Starter.java (main): closing the log file and exiting with error
	  on exception.
	* MainWindow.java (start): checking if RXTX classes are available
	  before showing the GUI, because otherwise the GUI is not shown
	  and the only error message is in the console or in the log file.
	* Utils.java (closeProgram): allow the filename to be null - the log
	  file, if any, is not touched.
	* THANKS: added more thanks for the software that made JYMAG possible
	* PhoneElement.java (getExt, getFilename): added null checks
	* PhoneElement.java: removed synchronisation from methods, because
	  there are no setter methods.
	* Utils.java (createOpenFileChooser): more checks for null.
	* test: added tests and the required stub classes.
	* PhoneAlarm.java (getDays): checking for null.
	* *Panel.java: makeing the buttons same height for better layout
	* README, manuals: added alternative addresses of RxTx
	* ConfigFile.java: enhanced detecting the system end-of-line sequence
	* ConfigFile.java (read): better performance in comment matching
	  (compiling the pattern just once).
	* DialPanel.java: disabling connection type and number controls when
	  manual command is selected
	* PhoneMessage.java: corrected the response match patterns

