	  of days contains 0, which means that all days should be enabled.
	* RawCommunicator.java (sendButActionPerformed): using a SwingWorker
	  to perform phone operations. Command area disabled during processing.
	* CapabilityWindow.java (getCapButActionPerformed): using a
	  SwingWorker to perform phone operations.
	* DataTransporter.java: added untested methods for sending, receiving,
	  deleting and getting the list of SMS messges (nothing more possible
	  because of the unknown format). Added methods for clearing and
	  setting the RTS and DTR signals. Added method for reading the signal
	  power. Added methods that check the state of the signals.
	* PhoneMessage.java: a class for phone message manipulation.
	* MainWindow.java (MainWindow): the videos', java's and alarms' tables
	  now also have mouse listeners that select all the rows when the user
	  clicks on the table header. Moved all transport-related code to
	  TransferUtils.java, removing the dependency on rxtx from this class.
	* TransferUtils.java: a new class with utility methods connected to
	  ports and transfering data.
	* Utils.java (createOpenFileChooser): a method for creating
	  JFileChoosers, moved from MainWindow.java.
	* Utils.java (redirectStderrToFile): a method to redirect the
	  standard error output to a log file, moved from MainWindow.java.
	* Utils.java (closeProgram): a method that closes the whole program,
	  moved from MainWindow.java.
	* Utils.java (TableMouseListener): added a listener class for table
	  header clicks.
	* Utils.java (updateStatusLabel, STATUS): a method for seeing the
	  status label and enumeration of program states, moved from
	  MainWindow.java.
	* README: added a method for building JYMAG with ant. Updated with
	  drag&drop. Updated with information about alarm clocks.
	* Utils.java (EscKeyListener): added a listener class for the Esc key.
	  Removed all the KL inner classes from the GUI windows.
	* DataTransporter.java (findBytes): fixed an ArrayIndexOutOfBounds
	  exception.
	* JYMAGTransferHandler.java: drag&drop support.
	* RawCommunicator.java: pushbutton for the RTS and DTR signal, labels
	  for the RI, CTS, DSR and DCD signals. Added the ability to send a
	  file to the phone.
	* SignalDisplayer.java: a window which displays the signal power
	  detected by the phone.

